claim.claim-text:
1. A system for analyzing compounds in a liquid sample, comprising: 
a) means for separating the compounds in said liquid sample; 
b) means for dividing said separated compounds into equal first and second portions; 
c) means for ionizing compounds in said first portion; 
d) means for ionizing compounds in said second portion; 
e) means for detecting and forming electronic signals corresponding to the positively charged ions in said first portion; 
f) means for detecting and forming electronic signals corresponding to the negatively charged ions in said second portion; 
g) means for combining signals from said first and second detecting means into data for both the positively and negatively charged ions; and 
h) means for displaying the data for said positively and negatively charged ions.

10. A method for analyzing compounds in a liquid sample, comprising: 
a) separating the compounds in said liquid sample; 
h) dividing said separated compounds into equal first and second portions; 
i) ionizing compounds in said first portion; 
j) ionizing compounds in said second portion; 
k) detecting and forming electronic signals corresponding to the positively charged ions in said first portion; 
l) detecting and forming electronic signals corresponding to the negatively charged ions in said second portion; 
m) combining signals from said first and second detecting means into data for both the positively and negatively charged ions; and 
n) displaying the data for said positively and negatively charged ions.
